    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>TRENTON HOTEL</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By KAREN DeMASTERS</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Demasters, Karen</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gov Christine Whitman attends ground-breaking ceremony for new Marriott Hotel in downtown Trenton, NJ (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Governor Whitman last week attended a ground-breaking for a new Marriott Hotel in downtown Trenton, which has not had a major hotel for the past 15 years. The hotel will be connected to the newly renovated War Memorial building near the State House complex. The $58 million project, to be built with the help of several state and local loans and grants, is to be completed by spring of 2002. The 200-room hotel also will include a 15,500-square-foot conference center and a 657-space parking garage.</p>
        <p>KAREN DeMASTERS</p>
      </block>
